               <msContents>
                  <summary>Kosovar author <persName xml:lang="tu" key="person_39160012" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/39160012/" type="standard" role="cmm" change="#role-assignment">Prizrenli Şemi Şemullah (fl. 16th c.)</persName> composed this Ottoman Turkish commentary on the Persian <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Pandnāmah</title> (Book of Advice), spuriously ascribed to <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard" key="person_120724759" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/120724759/" role="dub">Farīd al-Dīn ʻAṭṭār</persName>. 
                     In his introduction, the author states how he composed the work at the request of his friend ʿÖmer b. Ḥüseyin, which he dedicated to the latter’s patron Zeyrek Ağa then when completed, presented it to
                     <persName role="hnr" key="person_266879898" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/266879898/">Sulṭān Murād III (b. 1546, r. 1574–95 CE)</persName>. The commentary itself consists of verse by verse quotations, with their translations, and occasional glosses on the original
                     text. An Ottoman-era scribe named <persName xml:lang="tu">Ahmet Kadır Bülevi</persName> completed this manuscript <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari" when="1666-07-06">3 Muḥarram 1077 AH (6 Jul. 1666 CE)</date>. 
                  </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_889-item1">
                     <author key="person_120724759" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/120724759/" change="#ids-cleanup">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard" role="aut" change="#role-assignment">ʻAṭṭār, Farīd al-Dīn, -approximately 1230</persName><lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" role="aut" change="#role-assignment">‏عطار، فريد الدين محمد بن ابراهيم نيشابورى‏</persName>
                     </author>
                     <author role="cmm" key="person_39160012" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/39160012/">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard" role="cmm" change="#role-assignment">Şemi Şemullah, Prizrenli, active 16th century</persName><lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="alt" role="cmm" change="#role-assignment">Shim‘ī Sham‘ Allāh</persName> <lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="alt" role="cmm" change="#role-assignment">Sham‘ī Sham‘ Allāh</persName> <lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" role="cmm" change="#role-assignment">شمعي شمع الله</persName>
                     </author>
                     <editor role="hnr" key="person_266879898" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/266879898/"><persName>Murād III, Sultan of the Turks, 1546-1595</persName></editor>
                     <editor role="scr" key="person_f7845">
                        <persName role="scr" xml:lang="ota-Latn-x-lc">Aḥmad bin Ḳadır al-Būlavī</persName> <lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="tu">Ahmet Kadır Bülevi</persName> <lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="ota">احمد قادر بولوى</persName>
                     </editor>
                     <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" key="work_6859">Pandnāmah ma‘a Sharḥ-i Sham‘ī</title>
                     <title xml:lang="en" key="work_6859">Pandnāmah with Ottoman Turkish commentary by Şemi</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="ota" type="basmalla"><locus from="1b" to="1b"> برگ ۱پ (folio 1b):</locus>
                     شکر و سپاس بی قیاس شول قادر قیومه که لطفی بی غایت و کرم بی نهایت دن مفخر شعار نبوة دثار رسول‌لر کروردی.
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="ota"><locus from="66b" to="66b"> برگ ۶۶پ (folio 66b):</locus>
                        کین نصایح را بخواند او بسی که بو نصیحت‌لری او کیمسه چون اوقپیه الحمد لله علی التمام. 
                     </explicit>
                     <colophon><locus from="66b" to="66b"> برگ ۶۶پ (folio 66b):</locus>
                     قد وقع المراغ من تسوید هذه النّسخة الشریفة في ید عبد الضّعیف النّحیف احمد بن قدر البولوي المحتاج الی رحّمة ربّه الفنی غفر اللّه له ولوا لدیه و لجمیع المؤمنین والؤمنات والمسلمین والمسلمات امین فی وقت قبل الفقیر فی یوم الثلث من شهر محرّم الحرام. سنه سبع وسبعین والف. تکري رحمت ایلسون اول جان ایچون * فاتحه احسان ایده یازن ایچون.
                     </colophon>
                     <colophon>Completed by <persName role="scr">Aḥmad bin Ḳadr al-Būlavī (Turkish: Ahmet Kadır Bülevi)</persName> in the afternoon of <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari" when="1666-07-06">3 Muḥarram 1077 AH (6 Jul. 1666 CE)</date>.
                        </colophon>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>For other copies of the <title>Pandnāmah</title>, see Rylands <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_7405"><idno>Persian MS 895A</idno></ref> and <idno>Gaster MS 1500B</idno>.</note>
                  </msItem>
